Description: Web front end for the MonAst Asterisk monitor
 MonAst is a web-based real-time monitor for Asterisk PBX servers.
 .
 This package installs the PHP front end that renders call, channel,
 queue and peer status in a browser. It talks to the monast-daemon
 service (or a remote instance of it) over HTTP and needs a web
 server with PHP 8.2+ configured to serve /usr/share/monast-web.
 Example Apache, nginx and lighttpd configs are in
 /usr/share/doc/monast-web/examples/.

